coldpool 3.5-2 (In development)
----------------------------------------------------------------

FUNCTIONALITY CHANGES

- interpolate_variable() trims rasters to the extent with data 
  using terra::trim().


coldpool 3.5-1 (August 20, 2025)
----------------------------------------------------------------

NEW FEATURES

- Added temperature timeseries from Gulf of Alaska and Aleutian 
  Islands bottom trawl surveys that are used for Alaska 
  Ecosystem Status Reports. Internal data sets:
    - goa_mean_temperature
    - ai_mean_temperature
- interpolate_variable() makes rudimentary variogram plots.
- New cluster_spatraster() function to perform hierarchical
  cluster analysis on terra SpatRaster objects.
- New calc_fixed_depth_var_bt() function from gapctd to 
  calculate variable values from oceanographic profiles (casts).
- New ggplot2 theme: theme_timeseries_blue_strip().
  
DATA UPDATE

- Preliminary EBS shelf data update for 2025.

FUNCTIONALITY CHANGES

- theme_multi_map_blue_strip() now includes a strip.background 
  color.


coldpool 3.4-3 (March 7, 2025)
----------------------------------------------------------------

NEW FEATURES

- Added salinity rasters and time series as built-in data sets.

FUNCTIONALITY CHANGES

- Files from /data/ moved to /assets/ to allow lazy data.


coldpool 3.4-2 (November 15, 2024)
----------------------------------------------------------------

BUG FIX

- Fix error when interpolate_variable(bbox = NULL). 

coldpool 3.4-1 (August 22, 2024)
----------------------------------------------------------------

NEW FEATURES

- Added temperature isotherm extent as built-in data sets for 
  the NBS (see ?nbs_mean_temperature).


DATA UPDATE

- Update with 2024 survey data.


coldpool 3.3-1 (February 23, 2024)
----------------------------------------------------------------

NEW FEATURES

- Added kriging_cv() function to compare kriging methods 
  using cross-validation for ordinary kriging,co-kriging, and 
  regression kriging.
- Added estimate_z_expansion() function to estimate the vertical
  expansion factors for 3D kriging based on cross-validation.
- Added estimate_anisotropy() function for estimating 2D
  anisotropy in variograms using cross-validation.
- Added new file naming conventions and masking options to
  interpolate_variable(), which should deprecate data2raster()
  in a future release.